<br>
With your post, I noted that the tone had gone far enough beyond a discussion and into an argument that the entire thread might better be placed in the 'rants' forum.  It wasn't your post specifically, although that post did 'tip the scales' in my opinion.<br>
<br>
You'll note that I didn't move the forum.  I figured that, with the observation, folks might return more towards discussion and less towards argument.  That appears to be the case to me.<br>
<br>
Note that, while I might disagree with what you're saying, I defend your right to say it.  All I'll ever ask is that board rules be maintained and that rants stay in the rants forum (if that is indeed the case). <p>Denoi Fishwhiskers<BR>
