<br>
This issue seems to have some folks that feel very strongly about it (on both sides). A recent article on castersrealm outlined Mr. Vancouvering's take on &quot;change&quot; at the Verant HQ. I didn't know what to make of it to be honest. I know for a fact that the campaign to remove TLC from production servers was started and finished in a matter of months. But Verant seemed to get a lot of folks who voted against it. The article mentioned Verant had to be careful about who they were upsetting vs who they were pleasing etc.<br>
<br>
If I were verant looking at these threads it would look like a no win situation. I think the only thing we have agreed upon here so far is...<br>
<br>
1. Difficult and unreasonable are relative terms.<br>
2. Folks wouldnt mind if TLC were tweaked, and if it were, both sides would be watching closely.<br>
3. Chip and I are horrible spellers and massacre the english language.<br>
<br>
Well, I can't say we actually agreed on number three, but I doubt will get many disagreements on that. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <br>
